signature.instructions: To determine if the code in the provided BLOCKs requires direct modification, thoroughly review the code within each BLOCK to identify any instances where the handling of constructor terms (CTRs) involves storing both the constructor ID (CID) and arity in the Lab field. If such instances are found, note that these BLOCKs require modification to store only the CID in the Lab field, with arity information relocated to a global static object in C. If no such instances are found, conclude that the BLOCKs do not require direct modification. Provide a detailed explanation of your findings for each BLOCK reviewed.
